  "prompt": "Any social workers out there have trouble balancing wanting to be faithful and a \u201cgood Christian\u201d but also remain neutral and not violate SW values?",
  "response": "This is a common challenge for many social workers who are also people of faith. Social work ethics emphasize:\n- Non-judgmental practice\n- Client self-determination\n- Respect for diverse beliefs and lifestyles\n- Professional neutrality\n\nReligious beliefs can sometimes conflict with these principles, especially around topics like:\n- LGBTQ+ rights\n- Reproductive choices\n- Secular approaches to healing\n\nSuccessful social workers often find balance by:\n- Separating personal beliefs from professional practice\n- Focusing on client needs and empowerment\n- Practicing self-reflection\n- Seeking supervision or consultation when struggling\n- Remembering professional ethical codes\n\nWould you like to discuss specific strategies for managing these tensions?",
